qas.question: Who had a leading role in liberating Yugoslavia?
Who was Tito formally an ally of after WWII?
Who set up a spy ring in the Yugoslav party?
As early as what year was a spy ring set up in the Yugoslav party?
From what domination did Yugoslavia liberate itself?

context: Unlike other new communist states in east-central Europe, Yugoslavia liberated itself from <a4_0>Axis<a4_0/> domination with limited direct support from the Red Army. <a0_0>Tito<a0_0/>'s leading role in liberating Yugoslavia not only greatly strengthened his position in his party and among the Yugoslav people, but also caused him to be more insistent that Yugoslavia had more room to follow its own interests than other Bloc leaders who had more reasons (and pressures) to recognize Soviet efforts in helping them liberate their own countries from Axis control. Although Tito was formally an ally of <a1_0>Stalin<a1_0/> after World War II, the <a2_0>Soviets<a2_0/> had set up a spy ring in the Yugoslav party as early as <a3_0>1945<a3_0/>, giving way to an uneasy alliance.[citation needed]
